    "Cantrips redesigned as utility-focused racial magic (build 356). Initial 355 design was four damage cantrips (Mote/Frost Bite/Pebble/Mind Touch) -- felt flat, just element variants. User pivoted to a mixed utility/combat pool: (1) Detect Monster -- scans 3x3 around caster, logs each monster's name + level + (col,row), and reveals the tile. spell_type='detect_monster', new handler in characters.cast_spell + combat._execute_charged_spell. (2) Light -- 5x5 fog-of-war reveal around the caster. spell_type='reveal_fog'. (3) Hold Monster -- reuses existing 'debuff_target' + 'time_stop' status_effect for 1 turn (combat.py:199 already skips the monster's attack when time_stop is on); enables flee or free-attack. (4) Mind Touch unchanged (1 MP Psionic damage). can_cast_spells() gate relaxed: previously max_mana>0 AND max_slots>0; now allows casters with at least one cantrip in memorized_spells even at 0 slots (fresh elf at INT 12). Spell-casting-mode now routes back to game_loop instead of combat_mode after a successful out-of-combat cast, so Detect/Light work as exploration tools. Harness default cantrip pair = Hold Monster + Mind Touch (combat-relevant). Picker UI shows utility-cantrip metadata as 'X MP - utility' (no 'power 0' on Detect/Light).",
    "Elf cantrips + lowered casting threshold (build 355). Build-354 playtester surfaced an elf-cohort collapse: 30/45 elves never reached F2 because they start at INT 12 / 0 mana and can't cast their memorised spells. Three-part fix: (1) Elf mana gate dropped INT 15 -> INT 11 with a softer slope (was (int-15)*4+10, now (int-11)*3+5) -- INT 12 yields 8 MP, INT 16 yields 20 MP, INT 25 yields 47 MP. (2) Four new cantrips, 1 MP each, slot-free. (3) New player_cantrips character-creation screen between portrait pick and starting shop -- elves pick exactly 2 of 4. Non-elves skip straight to the starting shop.",
    "V (vendor) added to floor-connectivity guarantee (build 354). User: 'V should always be reachable.' Build-353 validation showed ~10% of F1-F4 deaths were on runs that never visited a vendor because V was walled-off from the spawn pocket. dungeon._ensure_d_reachable already carved corridors to D and W when they were unreachable from the entry tile; extended the target tuple to include V. Same L-shape wall-carve through walls (NOT through M/W hazard rooms, which the agent's BFS still treats as transit blockers). Vendors are the only weapon / armor upgrade path for non-caster races, so a no-V spawn pocket is as bad as a no-D one.",
    "Gear-upgrade vendor pull on F1-F2 (build 353). Build-352 validation: 11/14 base-Dagger F1-F4 deaths were from runs that NEVER visited a vendor with 250-800g unspent. Cause: wants_vendor only triggered on (healing_count < 2 OR needs_repair) AND gold >= 50, but the 4-potion starter pack keeps healing_count >= 4 through F1-F2, so the wayfinder never actively pathed to V -- it just descended past. New trigger: weak_starter_weapon (atk_bonus <= 2 = Dagger) OR weak_starter_armor (def_bonus <= 3 = Leather), AND gold >= 25 (Short Sword price). The cheap-upgrade gold floor is far below the healing-need floor because early floors yield 25g easily after 1-2 kills. With the build-352 vendor-buy priority already in place, every triggered V visit should now produce an equipped Short Sword / Mace / Iron Sword.",
    "Vendor upgrade priority promoted to fix F1-F4 attrition (build 352). Build-351 playtester found 58% of all deaths happen on F1-F4 (before tomb_mode is reachable), most at base Dagger (atk+2) / Leather Armor. Vendors stock Short Sword (atk+4, 25g), Iron Sword (atk+5, 75g), Mace (atk+5, 60g), Ring Mail / Chainmail def+4-6 -- but the old vendor policy bought them LAST (section 4), after cooking kit + rations + 6 healing pots + 25 food + 3 mana + 6 fuel + 5 scrolls + buff potions. The 150g UPGRADE_RESERVE then often gated out the buy. Re-ordered: stockpile -> EQUIPMENT UPGRADE -> scrolls/buff potions. UPGRADE_RESERVE dropped 150 -> 100 because we're now ahead of the scroll/buff buys that needed the cushion. Equip-from-inventory flow is already wired via has_upgrade detection (line 2601), so a vendor purchase translates to a stat boost two steps later.",
    "Tomb-raid strength gate loosened to recover depth (build 351). Build-350 a/b: UNDEAD share 73% -> 61% (-12pp) BUT mean depth F5.36 -> F4.19 (-1.17). Walk-out saved heroes who then starved out without the cursed-gear payoff that powered the F5+ push -- they died to *random-encounter* undead F4-F7 instead. Two gate loosenings: (1) level_ok floor+3 -> floor+2 (parity with the floor+2 guardian, was one above; the raid spawn is 1.0x stats so parity is fair, whereas the cardinal-guardian +3 stays put because those are 1.25-1.3x). (2) can_survive from 4 expected hits to 3 (alpha-strike window for a no-multiplier guardian). can_dent unchanged. Goal: reclaim cursed-gear payoff at borderline-strong while keeping the UNDEAD-death reduction.",
    "Tomb-raid strength gate + walk-out decline (build 350). Broad audit on build 349 showed UNDEAD/ELITE UNDEAD = 73% of combat deaths (54/74), concentrated F5-F8 where the raid-spawn outpaces actual gear/HP growth. Prior gate (`level < floor+2`) let parity-level heroes raid into a floor+2 guardian and lose the trade. Replaced with a three-number strength gate: (1) level >= floor+3 (matches cardinal-guardian avoid threshold), (2) strength + weapon.attack_bonus >= guardian_defense + 5 (we can dent), (3) max_hp >= 4 * expected_dmg_per_hit (survive an alpha-strike). All three must pass to raid. Added explicit walk-out branch when not strong AND at full HP -- step back to the '.' neighbour the agent arrived on (the 4-corner guardian spawn guarantees that's the only '.' direction). Wounded-and-weak still pays respects for the free heal. Decline-via-walk-out leaves the tomb intact for a later, stronger return. Smoke test: s=1234 elf F2 (Legolas the Bowyer) previously dead to ELITE UNDEAD MUMMY @ Lv4 hitting for 28/swing -- now F3@(15,10) HP 38/38 at T300.",
